            <div type="note" subtype="biographical">
                <head type="title"><persName corresp="#HCA">Haddon C. Adams (d. <date when="1971">1971</date>)</persName></head>
                <p><persName corresp="#HA">Haddon C. Adams</persName> made an important bequest to the <orgName corresp="#RUSKINGALLERIES">Ruskin Galleries</orgName>, <placeName corresp="#BEMBRIDGE">Bembridge</placeName>,
                    which came to the <orgName corresp="#RUSKINGALLERIES">Galleries</orgName> on <date when="1971-09-15">15 September 1971</date>, following <persName corresp="#HA">Adams</persName>&#x02BC;s
                    death on <date when="1971-06-14">14 June 1971</date> (although he had deposited some items, including diaries
                    of <persName corresp="#JJR">John James Ruskin</persName>, prior to his death). <persName corresp="#HA">Adams</persName>, a civil engineer and a friend
                    of <persName corresp="#JHW">John Howard Whitehouse</persName>, started collecting during a visit to <placeName corresp="BRANTWOOD">Brantwood</placeName> in
                    <date when="1928-06">June 1928</date>. Early work forming part of the <persName corresp="#HA">Adams</persName> bequest included the commonplace
                    book, MS<!--Entry needed here.-->; <hi rend="italic">Little Jack</hi>, with its
                    tracings; and drawings of <date when="1831">1831</date> (a tower, signed with initials and dated <date when="1831-01-09">1 September
                    1831</date>), <date when="1832">1832</date> (&#x201C;Tunbridge Castle&#x201D; [<title type="book" corresp="#JRWORKSLE"><hi rend="italic">Works</hi></title> 38:
                    288, no. 1698]), <date when="1835">1835 </date>(twelve drawings from the tour of that year), and undated
                    but possibly early copies of <persName corresp="#SP">Prout</persName>. Work by <persName corresp="#JJR">John James Ruskin</persName> associated with
                    his son&#x02BC;s youth included his diary for <date when="1833">1833</date>, and the drawing &#x0201C;<placeName type="building" corresp="CONWAYCASTLE">Conway
                    Castle</placeName>.&#x0201D; </p>
                <p>See <persName corresp="#JSD">Dearden</persName>, &#x0201C;Haddon C. Adams Bequest&#x0201D;.</p>
            </div>
